    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong>, once melted, add your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>peanuts</strong> with your <strong>red chilli relish</strong> and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook for 2-3 min or until the sugar has melted and caramelised, then transfer them to a plate and reserve the pan \u2013 these are your <strong>sweet chilli peanuts</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a small drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken breast </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is lightly browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>with your<strong> hoisin sauce</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>with your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>ketjap manis</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 15 min or until all the water has absorbed, the rice is cooked and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, boil a kettle</p><p>Roughly chop the <strong>sweet chilli peanuts </strong>and set aside to cool \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli peanut brittle</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can \u2013 this is your <strong>wilted spinach</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked through, increase the heat to medium</p><p>Push the <strong>chicken </strong>and<strong> rice </strong>to one side of the pan and drizzle a little <strong>olive oil </strong>into the other side, then crack your <strong>egg[s] </strong>in</p><p>Stir the <strong>egg[s]</strong> with a wooden spoon to break the <strong>yolk[s]</strong> and cook for 1 min until it resembles scrambled egg</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> and your <strong>blanched peas </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the lid back on and set aside for 1-2 min or until the peas are warmed through</p><p>Once warmed through season with a little <strong>salt </strong>and drizzle over your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>one pan hoisin chicken breast & egg fried rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pan-hoisin-chicken-breast-and-egg-fried-rice-with-peanut-brittle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top your <strong>one pan hoisin chicken breast & egg fried rice</strong> with the <strong>chilli peanut brittle</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
